    <h1>Cognitive Celebrity Scientist Talk</h1>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Write your introduction here. Introduce the cognitive celebrity scientist and briefly explain the significance of the YouTube talk you are analyzing.
    </p> 
Cynthia Breazeal is an American roboticist and entrepreneur known for her work in the field of social robotics. She earned her Bachelor's degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from the University of California, Santa Barbara. Cynthia developed the robot Kismet during her time in the MIT media lab. This was one of the first social robots, the kismet was designed to recognize and respond to human sentiments, further presenting robots to interact with humans on a social and communal measure. Cynthia founded a company Jibo, Inc. directed to expand social robots and recognize and respond to human interactions. Cynthia has contributed significantly to the field of social robotics, human robot interactions and artificial intelligence. She has also received multiple awards for her contributions to robotics.

    <h2>Analysis of the Talk</h2>
    <p>
       Some of her most important talks include  “The rise of personal robots”. In this TED talk Cynthia Breazeal discusses the development and the interaction of personal social robots and the impact they may have in human daily lives. This talk discusses the role of emotions and sentiments in human and robot relationships and the way they interact. She further discusses the challenges and opportunities that may be dispensed. The next pertinent talk Cynthia has presented is “The promise and peril of our gene editing powers”. In this talk she explores the comprehensive gene editing and the effects it may have on humanity. Lastly, her “Building machines that learn and think like people” is another very important talk in her career. She discusses the obstacles and breakthroughs in building machines that can learn and understand and think in ways that are human-like and very very similar to human interaction.

    </p>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
       	In conclusion Cynthia’s work in science and her specialty in robotics include groundbreaking theories and contributions. Her TED Talks and presentations have not only showcased the current state of social robotics but have also sparked discussions on the ethical and societal implications of these advancements. Cynthia Breazeal's legacy lies in her transformative impact on the convergence of technology and humanity, opening new possibilities for the role of robots in human lives. 

    </p>


